image.altText: A shirtless, muscular man lifts a bucket of water.

props.synopsis: The residents of Rainbow Lodge have committed multiple crimes and been in and out of prison for decades. For many, its program is their last chance to take responsibility for their actions and prove they're ready for the outside world – but one slip-up could land them back inside.

title.children: Meet the residents of Rainbow Lodge, the broken men with nowhere else to go

image.altText: Surveillance drone

props.synopsis: Former immigration detainees who were released after a High Court ruling have had their residences photographed using drones, the government has confirmed.

title.children: Drones used to photograph homes of released detainees, minister confirms

image.altText: Two dung beetles roll a ball of dung over dusty ground.

props.synopsis: The ACT government is encouraging farmers to use dung beetles to recycle the nutrients in cow dung into their pastures, with experts saying they improve soil quality and reduce fly numbers — and are cheaper than fertiliser.

title.children: In Canberra 30 years ago you couldn't eat outdoors without being swarmed by flies — the answer was dung beetles

image.altText: Hands holding up a coin

props.synopsis: Coin collectors have descended on Canberra to take part in the Royal Australian Mint's coin swap.

title.children: Coin collectors are swapping cash for collectible coins at the Royal Australian Mint

image.altText: woman standing in window smiling

props.synopsis: An ageing generation of single women who have raised children, and are often well-educated with careers and middle-class backgrounds, are becoming permanent residents of caravan parks amid the housing crisis.

title.children: At this caravan park, women aged over 55 have found a way out of the housing crisis

image.altText: Luke Jackson celebrates a Fremantle goal.

props.synopsis: Fremantle bursts out of the blocks against Melbourne, while Essendon will face a challenge in getting past the improved Gold Coast Suns. Follow live.

image.altText: Passengers mill about an airport terminal, with one in the foreground siutting on the floor beside a pink suitcase.

props.synopsis: Flight cancellations and delays are unavoidable — but what can you do when you're left stranded at the airport? Your consumer right to compensation depends on the cause of cancellation.

title.children: Flight cancelled? Here’s what Qantas, Virgin, Jetstar and Rex say you’re entitled to

image.altText: A close up image of Josh Frydenberg looking serious.

image.altText: A graphic showing four Ozempic pens, three of which have the brand name ripped out

image.altText: butterflies seen pinned to a black background.

image.altText: A police wagon parked on the street outside a block of flats.

image.altText: Crew members shake hands inside a military aircraft with rear door open.

image.altText: a photo of a man and two searchers

image.altText: Two women hold a bucket between them as they walk along a South Korean island followed by a woman in a cart.;

image.altText: A large spacecraft in between four large telephone poles.

image.altText: Em Rusciano in yellow and black houndstooth jacket over yellow top, with ornate jewelled earrings
